<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFBF6A00FCEE977D1DADBA73" bold="true" box="[786,941,292,321]" pageId="68" pageNumber="826">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBF6A00FC31977D1DD5BA5A" authority="Dobson, 1877" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1877" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vesperugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="826" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mnasutus" subGenus="Vesperus">Vesperugo (Vesperus) mnasutus Dobson, 1877</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="74FC3CA3FFBF6A00FC1A97121DEABABD" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3783319468" pageId="68" pageNumber="826">
“Shikarpur [east of Rohri], 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFBF6A00FCEE97371D51BABD" box="[786,849,366,399]" country="Pakistan" name="Sindh" pageId="68" pageNumber="826">Sind</collectingRegion>
,” 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFBF6A00FC8D97371DE7BABD" box="[881,999,366,399]" name="Pakistan" pageId="68" pageNumber="826">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFBF6A00FCEE97C71B5DB82A" blockId="68.[786,1378,292,714]" lastBlockId="68.[168,1377,720,3001]" pageId="68" pageNumber="826">
Normally included in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBF6A00FBA197C71ACDBA85" authority="Rafinesque, 1820" box="[1117,1229,414,439]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="826" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Eptesicus</taxonomicName>
, but now treated as the sole representative of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBF6A00FB0397E41D60B937" authority="Bianchi, 1917" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhyneptesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="826" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhyneptesicus</taxonomicName>
; its relationships remain uncertain, as it cannot be placed into any recognized tribe. Genetic studies appear to place it as sister to a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBF6A00FB6B94031B5FB949" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[1175,1375,602,635]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="993" phylum="Chordata" rank="tribe" tribe="Vespertilionini">Vespertilionini</taxonomicName>
and Pipistrellini, and it may be best placed into its own monotypic tribe. Three of the recognized races (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFBF6A00FE5F94891C08B9C3" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[419,520,720,753]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhyneptesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="68" pageNumber="826" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nasutus">nasutus</taxonomicName>
, matschiei, batinensis) have been supported by genetic data; they may form a cline of increasing body size from south to north. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
